00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:48,810
200,000.

287
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:50,640
200,000?

288
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:54,800
What kind of unfair clause is that?

289
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,560
Exactly.

290
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:58,040
But I signed it in black and white, so I have no choice.

291
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,900
I'm leaving now. Enjoy your meal.

292
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,080
What's going on?

293
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:54,050
Wanqing.

294
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:59,330
This piece should be played gently and affectionately.

295
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:00,720
Like a

296
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,160
sweet memory.

297
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,040
Mr. Chen.

298
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,000
I'm so clumsy.

299
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:09,920
I can never get these details right.

300
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,120
Don't worry.

301
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:18,980
Take your time.

302
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:25,940
I'll show you once.

303
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,320
You came back quite early today.

304
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,000
Of course.

305
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,120
Home is always

306
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:24,640
much more comfortable than a hotel.

307
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:57,420
What are you doing?

308
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:00,050
This suit is custom-made in Italy.

309
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:03,160
Since you call this a home,

310
00:25:04,120 --> 00:25:06,320
don't bring dirty things from outside.

311
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:20,520
I

312
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:22,600
won't argue with you.

313
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:26,850
On the contrary, I quite sympathize with you.

314
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,200
When women get older,

315
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:30,480
it's inevitable for them to be psychologically unbalanced.

316
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:32,400
Otherwise, how would cosmetics and luxury goods

317
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:33,360
have a market?

318
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:08,800
Feifei.

319
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:11,520
Your Satomi Ishihara makeup look last week was amazing.

320
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:13,050
It looked exactly like her.

321
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:14,920
Honestly,

322
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,500
not only did I watch it,

323
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,600
I also shared, commented, and liked it.

324
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:19,760
Pretty loyal of me, right?

325
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:20,560
Thank you all.

326
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,130
I'll keep working hard.

327
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:29,200
Jiangzi.

328
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,920
Your Spider-Man video has a good concept.

329
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:34,650
But what about the data?

330
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,800
The completion rate is under 20%.

331
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:39,730
The view-to-like ratio is 270 to 1.

332
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:41,780
And we lost a lot of followers.

333
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:42,600
I knew it.

334
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,720
No one watches this kind of video.

335
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,580
It has no laughs, tears, or drama.

336
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:48,100
What is there to watch?

337
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,680
We might as well shoot challenge videos.

338
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:52,610
The numbers wouldn't be this ugly.

339
00:26:58,480 --> 00:26:59,080
It's okay.

340
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,760
Finding our positioning

341
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,160
takes time to figure out.

342
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,610
Still not giving up?

343
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:34,720
Mr. Yang.

344
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,520
People can lie,

345
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,320
but data won't.

346
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:44,760
Why is it like this, Mr. Yang?

347
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:46,920
From the script to the editing of this video,

348
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:48,920
I really put a lot of thought into it.

349
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:50,040
I can tell.

350
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,040
So what?

351
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:53,900
The result is inevitable.

352
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:57,960
You knew the outcome, yet you still let me shoot it.

353
00:27:58,640 --> 00:28:00,080
If you didn't hit a brick wall,

354
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:01,410
would you have given up?

355
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,360
Even if this is the outcome now,

356
00:28:04,360 --> 00:28:05,960
I'm still not resigned to it.

357
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,720
Those clickbait videos,

358
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:10,120
though they can get traffic in a short time,

359
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,720
are meaningless to me.

360
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:12,960
It's not what I want.

361
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,520
In the self-media industry,

362
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:16,640
traffic is value.

363
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,880
This sounds cruel,

364
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,520
but it's the reality.

365
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,160
But I just want to film real life.

366
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:25,400
I just want to say what I really want to say.

367
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,660
Why should others listen to what you say?

368
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,920
Why do people adore Aiwei?

369
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:37,170
Because she has become the Aiwei she is today.

370
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:38,840
No matter what the current Aiwei

371
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:39,880
says,

372
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,540
it is taken as words of wisdom.

373
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:42,960
So do you understand?

374
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,210
It doesn't matter what you say.

375
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:48,480
What matters is who you are.

376
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:07,160
Hello, sir.

377
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,490
Who are you looking for?

378
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:09,760
Who's in charge here?

379
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,330
Based on the feedback data,

380
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,170
Castor's last promotion round

381
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:18,060
did exceed our expectations.

382
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:19,920
In the next promotional period,

383
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:20,760
we also plan to

384
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:22,360
increase the budget.

385
00:29:23,160 --> 00:29:24,220
That's wonderful.

386
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:25,720
This way we can explore more ways to cooperate.

387
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:26,880
You can't go in.

388
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:28,410
Sir, you really can't go in.

389
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,360
Who's the person in charge here?

390
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:32,120
Aiwei, he insisted on seeing you.

391
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:33,250
I couldn't stop him.

392
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:34,240
You are?

393
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:36,160
I am.

394
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:37,160
How can I help you?

395
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:38,480
Good.

396
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,640
I'm Jiang Lili's father.

397
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:43,280
How could you sign this kind of

398
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:45,160
unfair contract with my daughter?

399
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:46,290
She's a young person

400
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:48,480
working her life away at your company,

401
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:50,740
and you set a 200,000 penalty fee for her.

402
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:51,860
Tell me,

403
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:54,480
does this comply with contract law?

404
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,620
You're acting like bloodsucking capitalists!

405
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:04,520
Terminate my daughter's contract immediately.

406
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:06,880
If you want to terminate the contract, you can go through the normal procedures.

407
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:07,440
Xiaoyu,

408
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:08,720
take him to the HR department.

409
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:09,850
Okay, Sister Ai Wei.

410
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:12,120
Why did you come to the company?

411
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:13,080
Why can't I?

412
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:14,400
I'm sorry to cause you trouble, Ms. Ai Wei.

413
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:14,930
Let's go.

414
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,040
Wait a minute.

415
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:18,720
Sir.

416
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:21,000
I think you might have some misunderstandings.

417
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:22,040
But since you're here,

418
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:23,570
let's get things straight.

419
00:30:24,120 --> 00:30:26,040
First of all, for One Thousand and One Nights newcomers,

420
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:27,560
we have never set

421
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:29,480
a termination fee of 200,000.

422
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:30,920
Secondly,

423
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:33,050
your daughter's current value

424
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:34,760
isn't worth 200,000.

425
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:37,880
If you're not satisfied with our company,

426
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,040
you can take her away.

427
00:30:39,040 --> 00:30:40,440
It won't cost you a penny.

428
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:42,320
But please don't cause trouble in the company

429
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,120
and disrupt normal office order.

430
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:45,050
Okay? Thank you.

431
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,360
What's going on here?

432
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:47,760
Let's go.

433
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:48,160
We'll talk about it when we get back.

434
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:48,760
I'm sorry.

435
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:53,840
Sorry.

436
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:54,840
That's okay.

437
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:55,770
Let's continue.

438
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:24,000
Dad, why didn't you tell me you were coming to my company?

439
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,520
Do I have to tell you?

440
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:26,640
That 200,000,

441
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,100
you made it up, didn't you?

442
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,440
Since there are no penalty fees,

443
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:30,920
you are coming back with me right now.

444
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:32,160
I'm not going back.

445
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:33,680
Come with me.

446
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:34,720
I'm not leaving.

447
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:38,080
Why are you always like this?

448
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:39,880
Taking charge of everything

449
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,540
and making all the decisions?

450
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:43,160
Can you understand me just once?

451
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:44,240
Even just once.

452
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:48,120
In high school, when choosing between arts and sciences,

453
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:49,320
I wanted to study sciences,

454
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,520
but you insisted girls must study arts.

455
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,880
When applying for college,

456
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:54,360
I wanted to study in Beijing,

457
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:57,160
but you made me apply to a school in Changsha because it was closer to home.

458
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:58,360
After graduation,

459
00:31:58,360 --> 00:32:00,400
I wanted to come to Beijing to do social media.

460
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:01,920
Without even telling me,

461
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,720
you arranged a job for me at a magazine

462
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,400
so I would have a stable career.

463
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,920
I was only doing it for your own good.

464
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:09,160
Right, because you were doing it for my own good,

465
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:11,090
I never dared to rebel against you.

466
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,280
Why do you always arrange my life

467
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:16,960
according to your own ideas?

468
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,920
You never consider my feelings.

469
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:25,200
I'm almost thirty.

470
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:29,440
I just want to do what I like.

471
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:32,920
Dad, just let go.

472
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:36,120
Just let me be myself freely, okay?

473
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:19,160
What kind of father are you?

474
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,600
And you're asking me what's wrong?

475
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,880
It's Xiaoxiao's wedding.

476
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:23,340
Are you really not coming?

477
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:25,530
There's a problem with my visa.

478
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:26,960
I really can't make it back.

479
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:27,800
Besides,

480
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:29,600
aren't you there for the wedding?

481
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:31,040
With you helping her organize it,

482
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:32,370
I'm completely at ease.

483
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:35,360
All right.

484
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,140
I'm hanging up.

485
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:50,780
Come, have some fruit.

486
00:33:52,240 --> 00:33:53,570
He said he's not coming.

487
00:33:57,600 --> 00:33:58,200
It's fine.

488
00:33:58,560 --> 00:34:00,490
I didn't expect him to come anyway.

489
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:01,560
What about your mom?

490
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:02,960
Does she not know either?

491
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:04,680
I didn't tell her.

492
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:05,680
Since I was little,

493
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:08,010
I've hardly been in touch with her anyway.

494
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:09,730
It'd be awkward if she came.

495
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:13,040
As long as I have you, Auntie, it's fine.

496
00:34:13,120 --> 00:34:13,760
Auntie,

497
00:34:13,880 --> 00:34:14,920
come help me take a look.

498
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,719
Which of these veils looks best?

499
00:34:19,239 --> 00:34:20,440
Which one do you like?

500
00:34:21,679 --> 00:34:22,520
The short one.

501
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,239
The short one

502
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:25,929
does make you look younger,

503
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:28,360
but it looks a bit cheap.

504
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:30,560
Aren't you wearing a floor-length dress?

505
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:31,719
Choose a long veil.

506
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:34,639
Then I'll listen to you, Auntie.

507
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:39,080
By the way, Auntie,

508
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:40,880
do you remember my college classmate Jiang Lili?

509
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:42,199
She joined your company.

510
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:42,880
Jiang Lili?

511
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,199
She calls herself Jiang Zi now.

512
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:46,520
During my college graduation ceremony,

513
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:47,520
you even met her.

514
00:34:49,239 --> 00:34:49,719
Did I?

515
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:51,880
She said she came to Beijing this time

516
00:34:51,880 --> 00:34:53,120
just for you.

517
00:34:53,719 --> 00:34:55,880
Auntie, if you have any good resources,

518
00:34:55,880 --> 00:34:57,280
please introduce her.

519
00:34:57,840 --> 00:34:59,120
If she's suitable for this industry,

520
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:00,280
she won't need my introduction.

521
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,400
If she's not suitable,

522
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:03,930
she wouldn't be able to handle it even if I did.

523
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:05,520
That's true.

524
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,000
Where is Jintian?

525
00:35:08,680 --> 00:35:10,920
I think he went to the wedding company.

526
00:35:11,040 --> 00:35:13,640
Said there were some details to discuss today.

527
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:16,560
Is it your wedding or not?

528
00:35:16,560 --> 00:35:18,820
Leaving Jintian to do all the work alone.

529
00:35:19,080 --> 00:35:20,520
Auntie,

530
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:23,480
I hear people say

531
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:25,680
that marriage is the graveyard of love.

532
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:28,920
But seeing how affectionate you and Uncle have been for so many years...

533
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,360
How is it still so good?

534
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:31,200
How exactly did you do it?

535
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:32,280
Please teach me.

536
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,660
You just need to choose the right person.

537
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:52,520
Yuan'an North 1st Road.

538
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:53,850
Yuan'an North 1st Road.

539
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,240
Welcome back to my channel.

540
00:36:17,240 --> 00:36:18,880
Hello everyone, I'm Jiangzi.

541
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:21,340
I am currently on the top floor of a building.

542
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:22,520
Um.

543
00:36:22,720 --> 00:36:23,440
Jiangzi.

544
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:25,880
Did you watch the video?

545
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:26,320
No.

546
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:28,100
What happened?

547
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,220
Unbelievable.

548
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:30,940
Just to get famous,

549
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,600
he even drinks toilet water.

550
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:33,330
I've seen it.

551
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:36,360
That guy drinks more aggressively than I do.

552
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,220
Internet celebrities, you know.

553
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,160
Cheers.

554
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:42,720
Come on.

555
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:45,450
What are you talking about?

556
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:47,120
Watch your mouth.

557
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:49,400
Are you asking for a beating?

558
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:49,880
Let go.

559
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:50,640
Don't move.

560
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:51,640
All of you, let go.

561
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,120
Let go.

562
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:07,080
Hello, Auntie.

563
00:37:07,080 --> 00:37:07,400
Lili,

564
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:08,460
come over quickly.

565
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,130
Your dad got into a fight with someone.

566
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:13,280
Don't worry, don't worry.

567
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:14,640
I'll head back right away.

568
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:15,480
Is it serious?

569
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:16,970
Take it easy.

570
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:29,880
Honestly, what were you thinking?

571
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,720
People have their own mouths.

572
00:37:31,720 --> 00:37:33,040
They can say whatever they want.

573
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:34,120
Why do you care?

574
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:36,250
What if something happened to you?

575
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:38,260
I couldn't stand what he said.

576
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:41,800
All right.

577
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,820
What do you want for dinner? I'll order takeout.

578
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:51,160
Takeout again?

579
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:53,540
Takeout isn't nutritious at all.

580
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,280
I'll see what's in the fridge.

581
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,940
I'll make a few dishes for you.

582
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:04,960
Why is the fridge completely empty?

583
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:06,220
There's nothing in it.

584
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:08,600
Oh, you.

585
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:11,080
There's not a single vegetable in the fridge.

586
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,880
What kind of life are you living?

587
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:15,560
Young people leave early and come back late.

588
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:17,040
We all just order takeout.

589
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,000
It's fine, don't worry.

590
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,200
I will take good care of myself.

591
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:20,080
Take care of yourself.

592
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:22,240
Is this what you call taking care of yourself?

593
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:23,440
If you were in our hometown,

594
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,440
at least you'd have hot meals to eat.

595
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:26,560
Look at you here,

596
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:28,560
not knowing where your next meal is coming from.

597
00:38:28,560 --> 00:38:29,040
This,

598
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,000
is just...

599
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:30,640
Lili.

600
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:32,840
You're drifting in Beijing alone,

601
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:34,280
with no family or friends.

602
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:35,280
You order takeout all day,

603
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,720
and your job is unstable.

604
00:38:37,160 --> 00:38:38,760
How could your dad not worry?

605
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:41,880
I'm an adult now.

606
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:43,250
Don't worry.

607
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:44,940
You say that so easily.

608
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:46,920
How could parents not worry?

609
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:49,400
Now seeing you living like this in Beijing,

610
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,330
how could your dad sleep after going home?

611
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,610
Your classmate is back, right?

612
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:06,240
It's a guy.

613
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:08,040
Who is he?

614
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:13,000
My boyfriend.

615
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,600
Where's the tea? Help me find it.

616
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:16,620
Wait, what tea?

617
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,260
Who is your boyfriend?

618
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:19,560
This.

619
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:21,300
Oh my goodness,

620
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:23,200
how does she have a boyfriend

621
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:24,040
so fast?

622
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:25,680
Help me fool them,

623
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:28,170
and I'll move out immediately.

624
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:30,320
Is that a deal?

625
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:31,240
I swear.

626
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:34,840
You two don't need to make tea.

627
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:36,320
Come over and sit.

628
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:37,800
Come and sit.

629
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:40,600
Please.

630
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:41,660
It's a deal.

631
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:46,520
Look.

632
00:39:47,480 --> 00:39:49,480
I didn't even have time to introduce you.

633
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,480
Come, come, come.

634
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:53,720
This is my boyfriend.

635
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:58,160
His name is

636
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:58,960
Luo Xin.

637
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,080
This is

638
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:00,680
my dad and

639
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:01,320
my aunt.

640
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,100
Hello, sir, ma'am.

641
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:09,400
Lili,

642
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:13,080
didn't you say you were sharing an apartment

643
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,680
with your female classmate?

644
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:15,200
Well,

645
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:21,440
I was just afraid you'd worry.

646
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,920
Is he really your boyfriend?

647
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:29,900
He is my boyfriend.

648
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:31,680
We've been together for

649
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:32,480
a month now,

650
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:33,340
haven't we?

651
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:36,160
Yes.

652
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:38,280
We've been together for a month.

653
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:41,200
You've only been in Beijing for three months.

654
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:43,060
You found a boyfriend so quickly.

655
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:47,560
When it comes to love,

656
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,770
it happens fast.

657
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:50,100
You just can't stop it.

658
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:52,560
Who chased who?

659
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:56,120
He chased me,

660
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:58,520
but I made the first move.

661
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:09,970
What's your name again?

662
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:11,120
Auntie,

663
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:12,120
my name is Luo Xin.

664
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:14,040
Just call me Xiao Luo.

665
00:41:14,040 --> 00:41:14,680
Xiao Luo,

666
00:41:15,280 --> 00:41:15,880
Xiao Luo.

667
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:17,320
Where are you from?

668
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:17,880
And

669
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:18,880
where do you work?

670
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:20,080
How much do you make a month?

671
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:21,760
Auntie, that's his privacy.

672
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:24,360
You've been living together for a month.

673
00:41:24,360 --> 00:41:25,880
What privacy?

674
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:29,080
Right?

675
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:31,280
Is there something you can't tell us?

676
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:36,600
No.

677
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:37,480
No.

678
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:38,880
Then,

679
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:41,580
Uncle, Auntie, please wait a moment.

680
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:50,360
What should we do?

681
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:09,480
My IDs are all here.

682
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:10,560
Uncle, Auntie.

683
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:15,200
I graduated from Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications.

684
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,480
I worked in a tech company before,

685
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,650
and now I'm starting a business with a friend.

686
00:42:21,600 --> 00:42:23,600
You're starting your own business.

687
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:27,400
It takes a lot of courage

688
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:29,920
for young people to start their own businesses nowadays.

689
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:31,050
It's not easy at all.

690
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:34,480
How many people do you have in your company now?

691
00:42:34,560 --> 00:42:36,240
It's still in the early stages.

692
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:37,970
Not many, about seven or eight.

693
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:39,640
Early stages.

694
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:40,850
That's good.

695
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:44,300
The house purchase contract.

696
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:46,170
You already bought a house.

697
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:49,700
It's a pre-sale house in Yanjiao.

698
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:50,680
It's a bit far.

699
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,320
I know Yanjiao.

700
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:54,450
Houses there are quite expensive too.

701
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:56,760
It's amazing for a young man

702
00:42:58,400 --> 00:42:59,840
to be able to afford a house there.

703
00:42:59,840 --> 00:43:00,370
Amazing.

704
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:03,080
But Lili,

705
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:05,680
it's good for you to have a boyfriend in Beijing.

706
00:43:05,680 --> 00:43:07,880
So she won't have to go home alone

707
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:10,140
to a dark house without a single light on.

708
00:43:10,280 --> 00:43:10,880
Luo,

709
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:12,600
Lili is a bit

710
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:14,440
too stubborn.

711
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,160
She does things

712
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:17,160
rashly.

713
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:20,170
You'll have to bear with her in the future.

714
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:21,480
It's her tem...

715
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,000
I will.

716
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:25,360
Luo Xin is so good to me.

717
00:43:25,840 --> 00:43:27,160
He is very gentle,

718
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:28,920
generous and considerate.

719
00:43:29,600 --> 00:43:31,240
Even if I work in independent media in Beijing,

720
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:32,960
living precariously, I won't starve.

721
00:43:32,960 --> 00:43:34,960
Don't worry, he will take care of me.

722
00:43:35,720 --> 00:43:37,080
Yes, Uncle and Aunt.

723
00:43:37,680 --> 00:43:39,160
I'm here, I'll take care of her.

724
00:43:39,160 --> 00:43:39,840
Yes.

725
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:40,800
Rest assured.

726
00:43:44,280 --> 00:43:44,680
Well.

727
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:51,000
Very good.
